library(quantmod)
library(ggplot2)

x<-getSymbols("600036.ss",from="2014-12-01",to="2019-11-30",src = "yahoo",auto.assign=FALSE)#
y<-getSymbols("601166.ss",from="2014-12-01",to="2019-11-30",src = "yahoo",auto.assign=FALSE)#

df<-data.frame(index(x),x$`600036.SS.Close`,y$`601166.SS.Close`)
colnames(df)<-c("day","CMB","CIB")

ggplot(data = df,aes(x=day,y=CMB))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=day,y=CIB))

#
xw<-to.weekly(x)
yw<-to.weekly(y)

dfw<-data.frame(index(xw),xw$x.Close,yw$y.Close)
colnames(dfw)<-c("week","CMB","CIB")

ggplot(data = dfw,aes(x=week,y=CMB))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=week,y=CIB))

#
xm<-to.monthly(x)
ym<-to.monthly(y)

dfm<-data.frame(index(xm),xm$x.Close,ym$y.Close)
colnames(dfm)<-c("month","CMB","CIB")

ggplot(data = dfm,aes(x=month,y=CMB))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=month,y=CIB))

#
xq<-to.quarterly(x)
yq<-to.quarterly(y)

dfq<-data.frame(index(xq),xq$x.Close,yq$y.Close)
colnames(dfq)<-c("quarter","CMB","CIB")

ggplot(data = dfq,aes(x=quarter,y=CMB))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=quarter,y=CIB))

#
xy<-to.yearly(x)
yy<-to.yearly(y)

dfy<-data.frame(index(xy),xy$x.Close,yy$y.Close)
colnames(dfy)<-c("year","CMB","CIB")

ggplot(data = dfy,aes(x=year,y=CMB))+
  geom_line()+
  geom_line(aes(x=year,y=CIB))

#

Lemp=function(x,y,u=0.1) {
  U=rank(x)/(length(x)+1)
  V=rank(y)/(length(y)+1)
  sum((U<=u)&(V<=u))/sum(U<=u)
}
Remp=function(x,y,u=0.1) {
  U=rank(x)/(length(x)+1)
  V=rank(y)/(length(y)+1)
  sum((U>=1-u)&(V>=1-u))/sum(U>=1-u)
}
u=0.5
taildep<-function(u=0.2){
#day
x0<-as.numeric(x$`600036.SS.Close`)
y0<-as.numeric(y$`601166.SS.Close`)
L0<-Lemp(x0,y0,u)
R0<-Remp(x0,y0,u)
#week
x1<-as.numeric(xw$x.Close)
y1<-as.numeric(yw$y.Close)
L1<-Lemp(x1,y1,u)
R1<-Remp(x1,y1,u)
#month
x2<-as.numeric(xm$x.Close)
y2<-as.numeric(ym$y.Close)
L2<-Lemp(x2,y2,u)
R2<-Remp(x2,y2,u)
#quarter
x3<-as.numeric(xq$x.Close)
y3<-as.numeric(yq$y.Close)
L3<-Lemp(x3,y3,u)
R3<-Remp(x3,y3,u)
#year
x4<-as.numeric(xy$x.Close)
y4<-as.numeric(yy$y.Close)
L4<-Lemp(x4,y4,u)
R4<-Remp(x4,y4,u)

#
lambda<-data.frame(cbind((c(0,1,2,3,4)),c(L0,L1,L2,L3,L4),c(R0,R1,R2,R3,R4)))
colnames(lambda)<-c("frequency","low_tail","high_tail")

ggplot(data=lambda)+
  geom_line(aes(x=frequency,y=low_tail),color='black')+
  geom_line(aes(x=frequency,y=high_tail),color='red')
}

u

taildep(0.1)#red line is high tail dependence,black line is  low tail dependence

taildep(0.2)

taildep(0.3)

taildep(0.4)

taildep(0.5)

taildep(0.6)

taildep(0.7)

taildep(0.8)

taildep(0.9)
